-- Taiwan Stocks: Acer, Hon Hai Precision, Foxconn Technology Co.
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-05-11T07:22:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/taiwan-stocks-acer-hon-hai-precision-foxconn-technology-co-.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index fell 1.1 percent to 7,401.37, the
lowest close since Jan. 18. The gauge sank 3.9 percent this
week, the biggest loss since the period to Nov. 26.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) dropped 0.6 percent to NT$32, the
lowest since Nov. 24. April sales fell 11 percent to NT$25.27
billion ($861 million), according to a statement filed to the
Taiwan Stock Exchange.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317)  (2317 TT), a unit of Foxconn
Technology Group, retreated 1.5 percent to NT$86.40, the lowest
close since Jan. 16. Chairman Terry Gou said at a Shanghai
groundbreaking for the company’s new headquarters that he’s
aiming for at least 10 percent revenue growth this year. In
December, Gou said revenue would climb not less than 15 percent
this year.  Foxconn Technology Co. (2354)  (2354 TT) slumped 4.9 percent to
NT$97.50, the biggest decline since April 17. April sales fell
67 percent to NT$2.28 billion from a year earlier, according to
a statement filed to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
